%N A354372 Square spiral on a 2D square lattice, one term per cell, starting at the origin with 0; the digits of the four integers forming any 2 X 2 square add up to a square.
%C A354372 This is the earliest permutation of the nonnegative integers with this property.
%e A354372 The spiral begins:
%e A354372 .
%e A354372      14--18--34--19--40--15
%e A354372       |                   |
%e A354372      25   4---5--12---8  43
%e A354372       |   |           |   .
%e A354372      16   7   0---1  13   .
%e A354372       |   |       |   |   .
%e A354372      17   3---6---2   9
%e A354372       |               |
%e A354372      11--21--31--22--10
%e A354372 .
%e A354372 The digits of the four integers inside each of the four 2 X 2 squares that contain the initial 0 add up to a square: 0 + 1 + 2 + 6 = 9, 0 + 6 + 3 + 7 = 16, 0 + 7 + 4 + 5 = 16, 0 + 5 + (1+2) + 1 = 9. This is true for any 2 X 2 square on the (infinite) grid; the upper right corner adds up to 25, for instance: (4+0) + (1+5) + 8 + (4+3) = 25; etc.
